freeze /friːz/

(freezing,froze,frozen,freezes) 

1. V-T/V-I If a liquid or a substance containing a liquid freezes , or if something freezes it, it becomes solid because of low temperatures. 结冰 

例： If the temperature drops below 0°C, water freezes. 如果温度降到摄氏零度以下，水就会结冰。 

例： The ground froze solid. 地面冻硬了。 

2. V-T/V-I If you freeze something such as food, you preserve it by storing it at a temperature below freezing point. You can also talk about how well food freezes . 冷藏 

例： You can freeze the soup at this stage. 你此时可以把汤冷藏。 

3. V-I When it freezes outside, the temperature falls below freezing point. 结冰 

例： What if it rained and then froze all through those months? 如果那几个月一直下雨然后又结冰该怎么办？ 

4. N-COUNT Freeze is also a noun. 冰冻 

例： The trees were damaged by a freeze in December. 那些树被12月的一次冰冻冻坏了。 

5. V-I If you freeze , you feel extremely cold. 感到极冷 

例： The windows didn't fit at the bottom so for a while we froze even in the middle of summer. 那些窗子的底部关不严，所以有段时间我们甚至在仲夏时节也感到极冷。 

6. V-I If someone who is moving freezes , they suddenly stop and become completely still and quiet. 呆住不动 [书面] 

例： She froze when the beam of the flashlight struck her. 当手电筒的光柱照到她时，她呆住了。 

7. V-T If the government or a company freeze things such as prices or wages, they state officially that they will not allow them to increase for a fixed period of time. 冻结 (物价或工资) [商业] 

例： They want the government to freeze prices. 他们要政府冻结物价。 

8. N-COUNT Freeze is also a noun. 冻结 

例： A wage freeze was imposed on all staff earlier this month. 本月早些时候，所有员工的工资都被冻结了。 

9. V-T If someone in authority freezes something such as a bank account, fund, or property, they obtain a legal order which states that it cannot be used or sold for a particular period of time. 冻结 (银行账户、基金或财产) [商业] 

例： The governor's action freezes 300,000 accounts. 州长采取行动冻结了30万个账户。 

10. N-COUNT Freeze is also a noun. 冻结 [with supp] 

例： ...a freeze on private savings. …对私人储蓄的冻结。 

11.  →  see also freezing , frozen

